network

Class Node

  • java.lang.Object
    • network.Node
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<Node>

    public class Node
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<Node>
    Symbolises a node in a Network. Is identified with an integer id which is read from the node network file by Network.Network(String). Note: this class has a natural ordering that is inconsistent with equals.
    Author:
    mesch

      • dijkstraDist

        public double dijkstraDist
        The shortest path distance to this node from the origin where dijkstra's algorithm was last run. Together with dijkstraPrev holds all information to deduce the shortest path from some origin to any destination with demand to it.

      • dijkstraPrev

        public Node dijkstraPrev
        the predecessor of this node when the origin is implicitly given by the last node that dijkstra's algorithm was run on.

      • dijkstraVisitied

        public boolean dijkstraVisitied
        boolean used in Network.dijkstraMinPriorityQueue(Node). True when the node has been processed to its final state.
